Text.Value: You serve a perversion of nature. End this now, before I end you.
Tell Ethel I'm coming for her.
You are outnumbered and outmatched - stand down.
The hag charmed you. You don't know what you're saying.
I know you wish to hurt Auntie Ethel. I know the book is here. I will die before I let you touch a hair on her head.
And I know ten ways to kill you before you can blink. We doing this or not?
You removed my hex? Ah, that's annoying.
Ready yourself to attack.
Nicely played - but it ends here.
Tell the hag I'm coming for her.
Too bad - you shall be the dessert to my main course. HAH!
I don't know anything about this book. I have nothing to do with this.
They want to hurt Auntie - they have the book. I will die before I let anyone touch a hair on her head.
True cruelty rules with fear alone. Pathetic the hag had to charm you.
How cute - I see why Auntie has her eye on you.
I wanted to play a little longer, Auntie likes her toys broken. She's not going to be happy I had to get my hands dirty.
I'm sorry you lived the slave of such evil.
I don't matter. Only Auntie does.
'Your' hex ? You were behind this?
The others I will leave to rot in this house, but you? I will gift Auntie your corpse - wrapped in your own intestines.
Tell me who you are - now!
Hah! You have no idea how wrong you are. I have worshipped her for decades past, and will for decades more.
Please - Auntie has gifted me idiots twice your size to feast on. You are a mere appetiser.

Synopsis:
The dialogue is triggeredin 2 cases:
- when players cure Mayrina cursed by the hag spy. It is very unhappy that his curse was lifted and starts  combat with players.
- when players destroy the voodoo doll and Mayrina is not in the city

We need this dialogue so hag spy has a chance to explain that it was him behind Mayrina's curse.
